    },
    "h-2": {
      "@type": "slate",
      "plaintext": "When you need this",
      "value": [
        {
          "type": "h2",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "When you need this"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "p-3": {
      "@type": "slate",
      "plaintext": "If you're using React, Vue, Svelte, Solid, Next, Nuxt, or any framework with client-side reactivity, you don't need this. The bridge fires `FORM_DATA`, your framework reconciles the DOM, and only the changed nodes update. Contenteditable cursors, image loads, and scroll positions survive every edit \"for free\" because the virtual DOM diff doesn't touch unchanged nodes.",
      "value": [
        {
          "type": "p",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "If you're using React, Vue, Svelte, Solid, Next, Nuxt, or any framework with client-side reactivity, you don't need this. The bridge fires "
            },
            {
              "type": "code",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "FORM_DATA"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": ", your framework reconciles the DOM, and only the changed nodes update. Contenteditable cursors, image loads, and scroll positions survive every edit \"for free\" because the virtual DOM diff doesn't touch unchanged nodes."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "p-4": {
      "@type": "slate",
      "plaintext": "Server-rendered-only frameworks have no such reconciliation. If you naively swapped the whole content area's `innerHTML` on every `FORM_DATA`, every keystroke would destroy contenteditable cursors, reload images, jump scroll, and reset IME state. The editing experience would be visibly broken.",
      "value": [
        {
          "type": "p",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Server-rendered-only frameworks have no such reconciliation. If you naively swapped the whole content area's "
            },
            {
              "type": "code",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "innerHTML"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": " on every "
            },
            {
              "type": "code",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "FORM_DATA"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": ", every keystroke would destroy contenteditable cursors, reload images, jump scroll, and reset IME state. The editing experience would be visibly broken."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "p-5": {
      "@type": "slate",
      "plaintext": "The fix is to update only the smallest block that changed, and let the rest of the DOM stay untouched. That's what the bridge does when you set `renderEndpoint`.",
      "value": [
        {
          "type": "p",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "The fix is to update only the smallest block that changed, and let the rest of the DOM stay untouched. That's what the bridge does when you set "
            },
            {
              "type": "code",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "renderEndpoint"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
