    "p-13": {
      "@type": "slate",
      "plaintext": "For the bridge to swap `[data-block-uid=X].outerHTML` reliably, every block's **outermost rendered element** must carry `data-block-uid={id}`. This is Astro-only / server-only — reactive frontends don't care because their reconciliation finds DOM nodes via virtual DOM, not query selectors.",
      "value": [
        {
          "type": "p",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "For the bridge to swap "
            },
            {
              "type": "code",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "[data-block-uid=X].outerHTML"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": " reliably, every block's "
            },
            {
              "type": "strong",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "outermost rendered element"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": " must carry "
            },
            {
              "type": "code",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "data-block-uid={id}"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": ". This is Astro-only / server-only — reactive frontends don't care because their reconciliation finds DOM nodes via virtual DOM, not query selectors."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "p-14": {
      "@type": "slate",
      "plaintext": "The recommended pattern: write a `BlockRenderer` (or equivalent) wrapper in your templating language that puts the `<div data-block-uid={id}>` around every block before dispatching to the block's own template. Then block authors don't think about it — the wrapper IS the contract.",
      "value": [
        {
          "type": "p",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "The recommended pattern: write a "
            },
            {
              "type": "code",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "BlockRenderer"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": " (or equivalent) wrapper in your templating language that puts the "
            },
            {
              "type": "code",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "<div data-block-uid={id}>"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": " around every block before dispatching to the block's own template. Then block authors don't think about it — the wrapper IS the contract."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "p-15": {
